race.comment: UP AND COMER (2) resumes for a top metro barn and has the numbers to be winning if she's ready to go. Will race over further and kicking off at the mile shouldn't be an issue. She missed a nose in a recent Scone trial over 1100m and the 2kg claimer should secure a soft run from the inside barrier. The betting will be key. GREEN RUN (3) was beaten a nose at Muswellbrook and then tackled the Dubbo Gold Cup and didn't get into it at big odds. Finds a more suitable contest and can get back on track. OVERFLOW MISS (6) has been around the mark at country level and Cahill is a positive jockey engagement replacing the 2kg apprentice. She's in the mix. DRUNKEN SAILOR (4) has been plain his last two but his form prior reads well enough. Comes back in grade on a quick backup and needs to be kept onside.
